    parentName: "p"
  }, {
    "href": "/posts/power-of-stories/"
  }), "previous post"), " you may think that in order to move anywhere you have to have a goal.\nA lot of self-help gurus from Maxwell Maltz to Jordan Peterson straight out tell us that human is a goal-seeking creature and setting goals is an ultimate way of\nstorytelling. Well, obviously it\u2019s a simplification and I can\u2019t condense years worth of work and deep thinking of really smart and successful people into just one\nsentence. Yet, even though it doesn\u2019t cover all the nuances of their arguments, it\u2019s hardly a mischaracterization. Also, I agree with them more than I disagree,\n\u201Cwe live in stories \u2014 not in physical reality\u201D is verbatim out of Peterson\u2019s works and he attributes this to Jung. So let me lay out my arguments against two\nstatements:"), mdx("ol", null, mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
